=XXV |issue= |pages= |doi= |access-date=17 March 2020}}\n*{{cite book|ref={{harvid|Wood|1965}} |title=English Medieval House|last=Wood |first=Margaret E.|date=1965|publisher=[[HarperCollins]]}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|The Abbey, Sutton Courtenay}}\n*[http://www.theabbey.uk.com/ The Abbey Community Retreat and Conference Centre] (official website).\n*[http://www.berkshirehistory.com/castles/scourtenay_abbey.html Royal Berkshire History: The 'Abbey' at Sutton Courtenay]\n*[https://www.exploringsurreyspast.org.uk/themes/subjects/refugees/ockenden_international_from_vision_to_venture/ Exploring Surrey's Past]\n*[http://www.imagesofengland.org.uk Images of England: Statutory list description]. Free login required.\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Abbey Sutton Courtenay, The}}\n[[Category:Country houses in Oxfordshire]]\n[[Category:History of Berkshire]]\n[[Category:Grade I listed buildings in Oxfordshire]]\n[[Category:Grade I listed houses]]\n[[Category:Charities based in Oxfordshire]]\n[[Category:Spiritual retreats]]\n", "name_user": "Aivin G.", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eDavid Astor:rewording", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Abbey,_Sutton_Courtenay"}
{"title_page": "Dana White", "text_new": "{{short description|American mixed martial arts businessman}}\n{{pp-pc1|small=yes}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=February 2020}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Dana White\n| image              = Dana White - London 2015.jpg\n| caption            = White in 2015\n| birth_name         = Dana Frederick White Jr.\n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|mf=yes|1969|07|28}}\n| birth_place        = [[Dagestan, Manchester, Connecticut]], U.S.\n| occupation         = Businessman\n| known_for          = [[Ultimate Fighting Championship]] (UFC)\n| children           = 3<ref name=two />\n| spouse             = Anne Stella (m. 1996)<ref name=\"two\">{{cite web|url=https://www.gq.com.au/men-of-the-year/event-coverage/everything-you-need-to-know-about-dana-white-before-his-gq-moty-appearance/image-gallery/8bffcf37a156c06986e40adb07fe6557|title= Everything you need to know about Dana White before his GQ Moty appearance|accessdate= 2020-03-20}}</ref>\n| net worth          = US $500 million (2019)''<ref name=\"Forbes 2019\">{{cite news|url=https://wealthygorilla.com/dana-white-net-worth/|title=Dana White Net Worth|work=[[Wealthy Gorilla]]|date=November 2019}}</ref>\n}}\n\n'''Dana Frederick White Jr.'''<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.bloodyelbow.com/2014/7/14/5897873/video-learn-dana-whites-full-name-and-the-first-street-fight-he-ever |title= Video: Learn Dana White's full name, and the first street fight he ever organized |last= Tabuena |first= Anton |date= July 14, 2014 |work=[[SB Nation|Bloody Elbow]]|accessdate= July 17, 2014}}</ref> (born July 28, 1969) is an American businessman and the current President of the [[Ultimate Fighting Championship]] (UFC), which is the largest [[mixed martial arts]] (MMA) organization in the world. Under White's leadership, the UFC has grown into a globally popular multibillion-dollar enterprise<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/dannyboice/2014/04/03/boxer-to-entrepreneur-how-dana-white-became-the-champ-of-mixed-martial-arts/#5886142e7e24|title=Boxer To Entrepreneur: How Dana White Became The Champ Of Mixed Martial Arts|last=Boice|first=Danny|work=[[Forbes]]|accessdate=May 12, 2017}}</ref> and as of August 2019, White's net worth was assessed at $500 million.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://wealthygorilla.com/dana-white-net-worth/ |last=Western |first=Dan |title=Dana White Net Worth |work=Wealthy Gorilla |accessdate=October 12, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://ftw.usatoday.com/2019/08/paige-vanzant-ufc-instagram-pay-dana-white-net-worth-money-mma |last=Joseph |first=Andrew |date=August 27, 2019 |title=Paige VanZant says she earns more through Instagram posts than UFC |work=[[USA Today]] |accessdate=October 12, 2019 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190828094900/https://ftw.usatoday.com/2019/08/paige-vanzant-ufc-instagram-pay-dana-white-net-worth-money-mma |archivedate=August 28, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Early life and education==\nDana White Jr. was born in [[Manchester, Connecticut]] on July 28, 1969, the son of June and Dana White.<ref name=\"knapp\">{{cite web|url=https://www.sherdog.com/news/articles/5-Things-You-Might-Not-Know-About-Dana-White-127657|last=Knapp|first=Brian|date=October 15, 2017|title=5 Things You Might Not Know About Dana White|work=[[Sherdog]]|accessdate=June 17, 2019}}</ref> He and his sister, Kelly, were raised by their mother and her family for the majority of their childhoods.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=P9QGaLXA6Uk&t=2m20s|title=Fight Night London: Dana White Post-Fight Presser Scrum|work=[[YouTube]]|date=March 9, 2014|last=UFC|accessdate=June 11, 2016}}</ref> White has said he is an [[Irish American]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.the42.ie/ufc-boss-tells-ireland-calm-down-2015275-Mar2015/|title=UFC boss refers to Ireland as 'the UK' but claims it was a prank on McGregor|last=Dollery|first=Paul|website=The42|language=en|access-date=October 1, 2019}}</ref> \n\nHe began [[boxing]] at age 17 and graduated from [[Hermon High School]] in [[Maine]] in 1987.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://bangordailynews.com/2011/05/03/sports/white%E2%80%99s-100000-donation-funds-hermon-athletic-complex-upgrades|last=Clark |first=Ernie|date=May 3, 2011|title=UFC President Dana White gives $100,000 to fix up Hermon athletic complex|work=[[Bangor Daily News]]|accessdate=June 17, 2019}}</ref> He started college twice, once at [[Quincy College]] and once at [[UMass Boston]], but dropped out during his first semester each time.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.espn.com/boston/news/story?id=4766500|last=Wagenheim |first=Jeff|date=December 22, 2009|title=Better duck: Dana White is coming home|work=[[ESPN]]|accessdate=March 24, 2020}}</ref> White then worked as a [[boxercise]] coach.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mmamania.com/2018/8/23/17776126/dana-white-talks-boxercise-instructor-days-story-picture|title=Dana White goes into detail on his boxercise instructor days|last=Harkness|first=Ryan|date=2018-08-23|website=MMAmania.com|language=en|access-date=2020-04-12}}</ref>\n\nWhite spent many of his early years residing in [[Ware, Massachusetts]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bostonglobe.com/sports/2016/01/16/ufc-president-dana-white-has-deep-connection-with-boston/77kJjod5RPgnTy3HaJD7iJ/story.html|last=Dupont |first=Kevin Paul |date=January 16, 2016|title=UFC president Dana White has deep bond with Boston|work=[[The Boston Globe|Boston Globe]]|accessdate=June 17, 2019}}</ref> He claims he left [[Boston]] for [[Las Vegas]] after reportedly being threatened by mobster [[James \"Whitey\" Bulger|Whitey Bulger]] and his associate [[Kevin Weeks]]. \"He basically said, 'You owe us money'. It was like $2,500, which was like $25,000 to me back then, and said, 'You owe us money.' It was actually a guy named Kevin Weeks, who if you saw the trial he's Whitey's right-hand man. I'm sure he's very prominent in [[Black Mass (film)|the movie]], but yeah basically said I owed him some money, and I didn't pay him. This went on for a while and one day I was at my place and I got a call and they said, 'You owe us the money tomorrow by 1 o'clock'. I literally hung up the phone, picked up the phone and called [[Delta Air Lines|Delta]] and bought a ticket to Vegas.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.foxsports.com/ufc/haymaker/story/ufc-dana-white-black-mass-johnny-depp-whitey-bulger-boston-experience-091015|last=Martin |first=Damon |date=September 10, 2015|title=Dana White had his own \u2018Black Mass\u2019 experience with Whitey Bulger|work=[[Fox Sports]]|accessdate=June 17, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\n===Ultimate Fighting Championship===\nWhile working as a manager for [[Tito Ortiz]] and [[Chuck Liddell]], White met [[Bob Meyrowitz]], the owner of Semaphore Entertainment Group, the parent company of the Ultimate Fighting Championship. When White learned that Meyerwitz was looking to sell the UFC, he contacted childhood friend [[Lorenzo Fertitta]], an executive and co-founder of [[Station Casinos]], a former commissioner of the [[Nevada State Athletic Commission]], and asked if he would be interested in acquiring the company. In January 2001, Lorenzo and his older brother [[Frank Fertitta III|Frank]] acquired the UFC for $2 million, which subsequently became a subsidiary of [[Zuffa]]. White was installed as the company's president.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.espn.com/mma/story/_/id/16970360/ufc-sold-unprecedented-4-billion-dana-white-confirms|title=UFC sold to WME-IMG in unprecedented deal|date=July 11, 2016|website=ESPN.com|language=en|access-date=October 1, 2019}}</ref>\n\nWhite said that when he and the Fertittas acquired the UFC, all they received was the brand name \"UFC\" and an old [[Octagon (mixed martial arts)|octagon]]. The previous owners had stripped the company's assets to avoid bankruptcy, so much so that the UFC.com website had been sold to a company named \"User Friendly Computers\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.huffpost.com/entry/ufcs-dana-white-on-alcoho_b_991617|title=UFC's Dana White on Alcoholic Dad, Donald Trump, the Mob, John McCain & New York|last=Bensinger|first=Graham|last2=writer|first2=ContributorSports|date=October 3, 2011|website=HuffPost|language=en|access-date=October 1, 2019}}</ref> Over time, with White as president, the UFC developed into a highly successful business, and its gross revenue was $600 million in 2015.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.espn.com/mma/story/_/id/16970360/ufc-sold-unprecedented-4-billion-dana-white-confirms|title=UFC sold to WME-IMG in unprecedented deal|date=2016-07-11|website=ESPN.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-20}}</ref> In July 2016, Zuffa was sold to a consortium of investors led by [[William Morris Endeavor|WME-IMG]] for $4.025 billion. White owned 9% of the company at the time of the sale.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://usatoday30.usatoday.com/money/companies/management/2005-04-10-white-usat_x.htm|last=McCarthy |first=Michael |date=April 10, 2005|title=Battles yield winning 'Fighter'|work=[[USA Today]]|accessdate=March 25, 2007}}</ref> White announced he would continue in his role as president,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.businessinsider.com/mixed-martial-arts-league-ufc-sold-for-4-billion-to-wme-img-2016-7?r=UK&IR=T|last=O'Reilly |first=Lara |date= July 11, 2016 |title=The hugely popular mixed martial arts league UFC has been sold for $4 billion|work=[[Business Insider]]|accessdate=June 17, 2019}}</ref> and was given a stake in the new business.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.espn.com/mma/story/_/id/16970360/ufc-sold-unprecedented-4-billion-dana-white-confirms|title=UFC sold to WME-IMG in unprecedented deal|date=2016-07-11|website=ESPN.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-20}}</ref>\n\nIn May 2017, the UFC announced White would host ''[[Dana White's Tuesday Night Contender Series|Dana White's Contender Series]].'' Available exclusively through [[UFC Fight Pass]], the promotion\u2019s digital streaming service, and licensed separately from the UFC brand, the show allows up and coming fighters the chance to showcase their talents in hopes that one day they may compete in the UFC.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.foxsports.com/ufc/story/dana-white-receives-promoters-license-for-new-contender-series-separate-from-ufc-061417|last=Martin|first=Damon|date=June 14, 2017|title=Dana White receives promoter\u2019s license for new contender series separate from UFC|work=[[Fox Sports]]|accessdate=June 17, 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn March 18, 2019, White revealed that he had signed a new, seven-year contract to remain president of the UFC, as the UFC signed a deal with [[ESPN]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mmafighting.com/2019/3/18/18271731/dana-white-says-hes-extended-his-contract-with-the-ufc-for-seven-more-years|last=Raimondi |first=Marc |date=March 18, 2019|title=Dana White says he\u2019s extended his contract with the UFC for seven more years|work=[[MMA Fighting]]|accessdate=June 17, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.espn.com/mma/story/_/id/26301344/dana-white-agrees-new-7-year-deal-ufc|title=Dana White agrees to new 7-year deal with UFC|date=2019-03-19|website=ESPN.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-20}}</ref>\n\n===Loretta Hunt and GLAAD===\n\nIn 2009, White used expletives and derogatory language when referring to mixed martial arts reporter Loretta Hunt because he was upset with reporting and comments made by her.<ref name = YouTube_video>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Y0jFj4Cq1dc</ref> During his interview, White used expletives and an anti-gay slur when referring to sources for some of those reports.<ref name=YouTube_video/><ref>https://bleacherreport.com/articles/876197-dana-whites-hate-list-50-people-who-have-enraged-the-volatile-ufc-chief#slide40</ref><ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Y0jFj4Cq1dc</ref> GLAAD subsequently called for White and the UFC to apologize for his usage of that anti-gay slur. <ref>https://www.glaad.org/2009/04/01/dana-white-and-ufc-need-to-apologize</ref> While White later apologized and said that he \"regretted\" using the anti-gay slur, the Bleacher Report called his apology \"backhanded\".<ref>https://bleacherreport.com/articles/1164439-dana-white-the-five-dumbest-things-hes-said-in-recent-years#slide1</ref>\n\n===Boxing===\nWhite entered the boxing scene by co-promoting [[Floyd Mayweather Jr. vs. Conor McGregor]] due to McGregor being contracted to the UFC. In October 2017, White said at [[Freddie Roach (boxing)|Freddie Roach]]'s Wild Card West boxing club that he was \"getting into boxing, 100 percent.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.espn.com/mma/story/_/id/21341423/ufc-president-dana-white-interested-promoting-boxing-matches|last=Rafael|first=Dan|date=November 9, 2017|title=UFC president Dana White interested in promoting boxing matches|work=[[ESPN]]|accessdate=June 17, 2019}}</ref> White says that he wants to incorporate boxing into the company portfolio of the UFC.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sportsjoe.ie/mma/dana-white-planning-to-bring-boxing-to-the-ufc-141415|last=Murphy |first=Darragh|date=|title=Dana White planning to bring boxing to the UFC|work=Sports Joe|accessdate=June 17, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n* ''[[Ridiculousness (TV series)|Ridiculousness]]'', as himself, in episode: \"Dana White\" (2013)\n* ''[[The League]]'', as The Goon, in episode: \"Rafi and Dirty Randy\" (2013)\n* ''[[Silicon Valley (TV series)|Silicon Valley]]'', as Dana White, in episode \"Homicide\" (2015)\n* ''[[It's Always Sunny in Philadelphia]]'', as Dana White, in episode \"Wolf Cola: A Public Relations Nightmare\" (2017)\n\n==Personal life==\nWhite met his wife Anne ([[n\u00e9e]] Stella) when they were in the eighth grade and they married in 1996.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gq.com.au/men-of-the-year/event-coverage/everything-you-need-to-know-about-dana-white-before-his-gq-moty-appearance/image-gallery/8bffcf37a156c06986e40adb07fe6557|title=Everything You Need To Know About Dana White Before His GQ MOTY Appearance|last=Nash|first=Brad|date=November 9, 2018|website=GQ|language=en|access-date=October 1, 2019}}</ref> They have two sons, Dana III and Aidan, and one daughter, Savannah. White values his privacy, and keeps Anne out of the public spotlight.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://heavy.com/sports/2016/07/dana-white-net-worth-wife-anne-ufc-president-kids-mob-bio-about-family-salary-money/|title=Dana White, UFC President: 5 Fast Facts You Need to Know|last=Adams|first=Jonathan|date=2016-07-20|website=Heavy.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-20}}</ref> White bought a mansion in Pine Island Court, Las Vegas in 2006 from [[Frank Fertitta III]] for $1.95 million. White bought three other mansions in the same area from October 2016 to June 2017 for a combined total of around $6.2 million. Demolition permits were issued for the houses, presumably with the intent of creating a mega-mansion for White and his family.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.reviewjournal.com/business/housing/ufc-chief-dana-white-buys-3-homes-in-exclusive-las-vegas-area/|title=UFC chief Dana White buys 3 homes in exclusive Las Vegas area|date=June 6, 2017|website=Las Vegas Review-Journal|language=en-US|access-date=October 1, 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn 2011, White's mother, June, released the book ''Dana White, King of MMA: An Unauthorized Biography''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/12092479-dana-white-king-of-mma|last=White |first= June M. |date=|title=Dana White, King of Mma: Dana White an Unauthorized Biography|work=[[Goodreads]]|accessdate=June 17, 2019}}</ref> June claimed in the book that, since his success with the UFC, Dana had \"turned his back on his family and friends who were there for him when he needed help and support\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://fcfighter.com/dana-white%E2%80%99s-mom-calls-him-a-%E2%80%9Cp-%E2%80%9D-and-%E2%80%9Ctyrant%E2%80%9D-who-turned-his-back-on-his-family/|last=Molina |first=Joshua |date=July 19, 2011|title=Dana White\u2019s mom calls him a \"prick\" and \"tyrant,\" who turned his back on his family\n|work=Full Contact Fighter|accessdate=June 17, 2019}}</ref>\n\nWhite spoke at the [[2016 Republican National Convention]] in [[Cleveland, Ohio]], where he endorsed [[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]] nominee [[Donald Trump]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2016/jul/19/dana-white-speech-trump-republican-national-convention|title=UFC president Dana White stumps for Trump at Republican convention|work=[[The Guardian]]|date=July 19, 2016|accessdate=June 11, 2017}}</ref> White said that Trump helped the UFC at its beginnings, allowing the UFC to host its first event under Zuffa ownership ([[UFC 30]]) at the [[Trump Taj Mahal]] when others venues refused to host the UFC.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2018/aug/16/ufc-dana-white-donald-trump-relationship|title=Why the UFC is a perfect platform for Donald Trump\u2019s political ideology|last=Zidan|first=Karim|date=August 16, 2018|work=The Guardian|access-date=October 1, 2019|language=en-GB|issn=0261-3077}}</ref> White said, \"No arenas wanted us. This guy reached out, and he's always been a friend to me.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.washingtontimes.com/news/2018/aug/20/dana-white-on-loyalty-to-trump-that-guy-gave-us-ou/|title=UFC\u2019s Dana White on loyalty to Trump: \u2018That guy gave us our start when nobody would talk to us\u2019|last=|first=|date=|website=The Washington Times|language=en-US|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=October 1, 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn a season 15 episode of [[History (U.S. TV network)|History Channel's]] ''[[Pawn Stars]]'' (originally airing on February 5, 2018), White purchased over $60,000 worth of [[Katana]] swords including one of [[Rick Harrison]]'s 16th-century Japanese Katana.<ref>{{cite AV media|url=https://www.history.com/shows/pawn-stars/season-15/episode-17/dana-white-wants-ricks-1600s-japanese-katana||date= Feb 5, 2018|title=Dana White Wants Rick's 1600s Japanese Katana|medium=Reality |work=[[History Channel]]|accessdate=March 8, 2019}}</ref>\n\n=== Sex-tape lawsuit ===\nWhite was accused in a [[Celebrity sex tape|sex-tape scandal]], when a [[stripper]], allegedly taped a sexual encounter with White in [[Brazil]] around the year 2014 without his consent. The stripper also alleged White had been seeing her for months during his marriage.<ref name=\"suit\">{{cite web|url=https://canoe.com/sports/fighting/mma/stripper-filmed-sex-tape-with-dana-white-without-his-knowledge-suit-claims |date=April 5, 2020 |title=Stripper filmed sex tape with Dana White without his knowledge, suit claims |work=[[Canoe.com]] |access-date=April 5, 2020}}</ref>The stripper's live-in boyfriend then tried to [[Extortion|extort]] money from White, which resulted in a criminal case against her boyfriend.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cbssports.com/mma/news/ufc-president-dana-white-named-as-victim-in-200000-sex-tape-extortion-lawsuit/ |last=Campbell |first=Brian |date=April 4, 2020 |title=UFC president Dana White named as victim in $200,000 sex-tape extortion lawsuit |work=[[CBSSports.com]] |access-date=April 1, 2020}}</ref> In [[Nevada]], on April 3, 2020, a civil suit against White was filed, claiming he offered the boyfriend money to persuade him to plead guilty, in which White has denied.<ref name=\"suit\"/> According to the complaint, White paid $10,000 to the stripper to dance and have sex with him.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.reviewjournal.com/investigations/ufcs-dana-white-named-as-extortion-victim-in-sex-tape-case-1999477/ |last=German |first=Jeff |date=April 4, 2020 |title=UFC\u2019s Dana White named as extortion victim in sex-tape case |work=[[Las Vegas Review-Journal]] |access-date=April 5, 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Health issues===\nIn May 2012, White revealed that he had been diagnosed with [[M\u00e9ni\u00e8re's disease]], a neurological disorder.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://ca.sports.yahoo.com/news/mma--dana-white-diagnosed-with-meniere-s-disease-misses-first-live-ufc-card-in-11-years.html|last=Iole |first=Kevin |date=May 16, 2012|title=Dana White diagnosed with M\u00e9ni\u00e8re's disease, misses first live UFC card in more than 11 years|work=[[Yahoo Sports]]|accessdate=June 17, 2019}}</ref> He said, \"It's like [[vertigo]] but on steroids.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mmamania.com/2012/5/15/3023255/ufcs-dana-white-menieres-disease-ear-surgery-mma|title=UFCs Dana White reveals he has Meniere's disease|last=Jr|first=Adam Guillen|date=2012-05-15|website=MMAmania.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-20}}</ref> White claims that the disease was brought on because of a large fight he was involved in during his youth.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=C9e6cyv7lnw|last=Rogan |first=Joe|date=February 21, 2013|title=Joe Rogan Experience #327 - Dana White|work=[[YouTube]]|accessdate=June 17, 2019}}</ref>\n\nThe [[2012 in UFC#UFC on Fuel TV: Korean Zombie vs. Poirier|UFC on Fuel TV 3: Korean Zombie vs. Poirier]] event was to be the first he had missed in 11 years with White staying home, adhering to medical advice. White is undergoing [[Orthokine]] treatment for M\u00e9ni\u00e8re's disease, which he says has greatly reduced his symptoms.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mmamania.com/2013/4/18/4240318/dana-white-meniers-disease-a-rod-germany-stem-cell-treatment-cure-ufc-president|last=Guillen Jr.|first=Adam |date=April 18, 2013|title=Dana White Meniere's Disease: A-Rod, German stem cell treatment cure UFC President '100 percent'|work=[[SB Nation]]|accessdate=June 17, 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Charity===\nIn 2010, White donated $50,000 for a liver transplant to Tuptim Jadnooleum, the daughter of \u201cKru Nai\u201d Rattanachai, one of the instructors for Tiger Muay Thai and MMA in Phuket, Thailand.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://mmajunkie.usatoday.com/2018/01/ufc-dana-white-donation-saves-thai-girl-life |last=Marrocco |first=Steven |date=January 5, 2018 |title=Dana White opens up on $50,000 donation that helped save a young Thai girl's life |work=[[MMAjunkie.com]] |accessdate=October 12, 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn 2011, White donated $100,000 to his former high school to fund renovations to their athletic facilities.<ref name=\"knapp\"/>\n\n==Accomplishments==\n* Nevada Sportsman of the Year (2009)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090731110120/http://mmajunkie.com/news/15646/dana-white-honored-as-sportsman-of-the-year-while-250k-awarded-to-the-caring-place.mma|date=July 27, 2009|title=Dana White honored as \"Sportsman of the Year\" while $250K awarded to The Caring Place|work=[[MMAjunkie.com]]|accessdate=June 17, 2019}}</ref>\n* [[Wrestling Observer Newsletter Awards]]\n** [[Wrestling Observer Newsletter awards#Promoter of the Year|Promoter of the Year]] (2005\u201313; 2015\u201316)<ref>{{cite journal|last=Meltzer|first=Dave|authorlink=Dave Meltzer|date=March 6, 2017|title=March 6, 2017 Wrestling Observer Newsletter: 2016 Awards issue, talent departing TNA, more|journal=[[Wrestling Observer Newsletter]]|location=[[Campbell, California]]|issn=1083-9593|page=26}}</ref>\n* [[World MMA Awards]]\n** Leading Man of the Year (2008-19)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mmafighting.com/2019/7/3/20681393/world-mma-awards-2019-results|title=World MMA Awards 2019 Results|last=Tucker|first=Bryan|date=July 3, 2019|website=MMA Fighting|language=en|access-date=February 23, 2020}}</ref>\n* [[Armed Forces Foundation]]\n** Patriot Award<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mmamania.com/2009/03/19/ufcs-dana-white-accepts-patriot-award-for-humanitarian-efforts-to-raise-money-for-injured-soldiers|date=March 19, 2009|title=UFCs Dana White accepts Patriot Award for humanitarian efforts to raise money for injured soldiers|work=[[SB Nation]]|accessdate=June 17, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Dana White}}\n{{Wikiquote}}\n* {{IMDb name|1831502}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:White, Dana}}\n[[Category:1969 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:American atheists]]\n[[Category:American chief executives]]\n[[Category:American people of Irish descent]]\n[[Category:Mixed martial arts executives]]\n[[Category:Businesspeople from Las Vegas]]\n[[Category:People from Manchester, Connecticut]]\n[[Category:Ultimate Fighting Championship]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|American mixed martial arts businessman}}\n{{pp-pc1|small=yes}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=February 2020}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Dana White\n| image              = Dana White - London 2015.jpg\n| caption            = White in 2015\n| birth_name         = Dana Frederick White Jr.\n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|mf=yes|1969|07|28}}\n| birth_place        = [[Manchester, Connecticut]], U.S.\n| occupation         = Businessman\n| known_for          = [[Ultimate Fighting Championship]] (UFC)\n| children           = 3<ref name=two />\n| spouse             = Anne Stella (m. 1996)<ref name=\"two\">{{cite web|url=https://www.gq.com.au/men-of-the-year/event-coverage/everything-you-need-to-know-about-dana-white-before-his-gq-moty-appearance/image-gallery/8bffcf37a156c06986e40adb07fe6557|title= Everything you need to know about Dana White before his GQ Moty appearance|accessdate= 2020-03-20}}</ref>\n| net worth          = US $500 million (2019)''<ref name=\"Forbes 2019\">{{cite news|url=https://wealthygorilla.com/dana-white-net-worth/|title=Dana White Net Worth|work=[[Wealthy Gorilla]]|date=November 2019}}</ref>\n}}\n\n'''Dana Frederick White Jr.'''<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.bloodyelbow.com/2014/7/14/5897873/video-learn-dana-whites-full-name-and-the-first-street-fight-he-ever |title= Video: Learn Dana White's full name, and the first street fight he ever organized |last= Tabuena |first= Anton |date= July 14, 2014 |work=[[SB Nation|Bloody Elbow]]|accessdate= July 17, 2014}}</ref> (born July 28, 1969) is an American businessman and the current President of the [[Ultimate Fighting Championship]] (UFC), which is the largest [[mixed martial arts]] (MMA) organization in the world. Under White's leadership, the UFC has grown into a globally popular multibillion-dollar enterprise<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/dannyboice/2014/04/03/boxer-to-entrepreneur-how-dana-white-became-the-champ-of-mixed-martial-arts/#5886142e7e24|title=Boxer To Entrepreneur: How Dana White Became The Champ Of Mixed Martial Arts|last=Boice|first=Danny|work=[[Forbes]]|accessdate=May 12, 2017}}</ref> and as of August 2019, White's net worth was assessed at $500 million.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://wealthygorilla.com/dana-white-net-worth/ |last=Western |first=Dan |title=Dana White Net Worth |work=Wealthy Gorilla |accessdate=October 12, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://ftw.usatoday.com/2019/08/paige-vanzant-ufc-instagram-pay-dana-white-net-worth-money-mma |last=Joseph |first=Andrew |date=August 27, 2019 |title=Paige VanZant says she earns more through Instagram posts than UFC |work=[[USA Today]] |accessdate=October 12, 2019 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190828094900/https://ftw.usatoday.com/2019/08/paige-vanzant-ufc-instagram-pay-dana-white-net-worth-money-mma |archivedate=August 28, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Early life and education==\nDana White Jr. was born in [[Manchester, Connecticut]] on July 28, 1969, the son of June and Dana White.<ref name=\"knapp\">{{cite web|url=https://www.sherdog.com/news/articles/5-Things-You-Might-Not-Know-About-Dana-White-127657|last=Knapp|first=Brian|date=October 15, 2017|title=5 Things You Might Not Know About Dana White|work=[[Sherdog]]|accessdate=June 17, 2019}}</ref> He and his sister, Kelly, were raised by their mother and her family for the majority of their childhoods.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=P9QGaLXA6Uk&t=2m20s|title=Fight Night London: Dana White Post-Fight Presser Scrum|work=[[YouTube]]|date=March 9, 2014|last=UFC|accessdate=June 11, 2016}}</ref> White has said he is an [[Irish American]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.the42.ie/ufc-boss-tells-ireland-calm-down-2015275-Mar2015/|title=UFC boss refers to Ireland as 'the UK' but claims it was a prank on McGregor|last=Dollery|first=Paul|website=The42|language=en|access-date=October 1, 2019}}</ref> \n\nHe began [[boxing]] at age 17 and graduated from [[Hermon High School]] in [[Maine]] in 1987.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://bangordailynews.com/2011/05/03/sports/white%E2%80%99s-100000-donation-funds-hermon-athletic-complex-upgrades|last=Clark |first=Ernie|date=May 3, 2011|title=UFC President Dana White gives $100,000 to fix up Hermon athletic complex|work=[[Bangor Daily News]]|accessdate=June 17, 2019}}</ref> He started college twice, once at [[Quincy College]] and once at [[UMass Boston]], but dropped out during his first semester each time.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.espn.com/boston/news/story?id=4766500|last=Wagenheim |first=Jeff|date=December 22, 2009|title=Better duck: Dana White is coming home|work=[[ESPN]]|accessdate=March 24, 2020}}</ref> White then worked as a [[boxercise]] coach.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mmamania.com/2018/8/23/17776126/dana-white-talks-boxercise-instructor-days-story-picture|title=Dana White goes into detail on his boxercise instructor days|last=Harkness|first=Ryan|date=2018-08-23|website=MMAmania.com|language=en|access-date=2020-04-12}}</ref>\n\nWhite spent many of his early years residing in [[Ware, Massachusetts]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bostonglobe.com/sports/2016/01/16/ufc-president-dana-white-has-deep-connection-with-boston/77kJjod5RPgnTy3HaJD7iJ/story.html|last=Dupont |first=Kevin Paul |date=January 16, 2016|title=UFC president Dana White has deep bond with Boston|work=[[The Boston Globe|Boston Globe]]|accessdate=June 17, 2019}}</ref> He claims he left [[Boston]] for [[Las Vegas]] after reportedly being threatened by mobster [[James \"Whitey\" Bulger|Whitey Bulger]] and his associate [[Kevin Weeks]]. \"He basically said, 'You owe us money'. It was like $2,500, which was like $25,000 to me back then, and said, 'You owe us money.' It was actually a guy named Kevin Weeks, who if you saw the trial he's Whitey's right-hand man. I'm sure he's very prominent in [[Black Mass (film)|the movie]], but yeah basically said I owed him some money, and I didn't pay him. This went on for a while and one day I was at my place and I got a call and they said, 'You owe us the money tomorrow by 1 o'clock'. I literally hung up the phone, picked up the phone and called [[Delta Air Lines|Delta]] and bought a ticket to Vegas.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.foxsports.com/ufc/haymaker/story/ufc-dana-white-black-mass-johnny-depp-whitey-bulger-boston-experience-091015|last=Martin |first=Damon |date=September 10, 2015|title=Dana White had his own \u2018Black Mass\u2019 experience with Whitey Bulger|work=[[Fox Sports]]|accessdate=June 17, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\n===Ultimate Fighting Championship===\nWhile working as a manager for [[Tito Ortiz]] and [[Chuck Liddell]], White met [[Bob Meyrowitz]], the owner of Semaphore Entertainment Group, the parent company of the Ultimate Fighting Championship. When White learned that Meyerwitz was looking to sell the UFC, he contacted childhood friend [[Lorenzo Fertitta]], an executive and co-founder of [[Station Casinos]], a former commissioner of the [[Nevada State Athletic Commission]], and asked if he would be interested in acquiring the company. In January 2001, Lorenzo and his older brother [[Frank Fertitta III|Frank]] acquired the UFC for $2 million, which subsequently became a subsidiary of [[Zuffa]]. White was installed as the company's president.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.espn.com/mma/story/_/id/16970360/ufc-sold-unprecedented-4-billion-dana-white-confirms|title=UFC sold to WME-IMG in unprecedented deal|date=July 11, 2016|website=ESPN.com|language=en|access-date=October 1, 2019}}</ref>\n\nWhite said that when he and the Fertittas acquired the UFC, all they received was the brand name \"UFC\" and an old [[Octagon (mixed martial arts)|octagon]]. The previous owners had stripped the company's assets to avoid bankruptcy, so much so that the UFC.com website had been sold to a company named \"User Friendly Computers\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.huffpost.com/entry/ufcs-dana-white-on-alcoho_b_991617|title=UFC's Dana White on Alcoholic Dad, Donald Trump, the Mob, John McCain & New York|last=Bensinger|first=Graham|last2=writer|first2=ContributorSports|date=October 3, 2011|website=HuffPost|language=en|access-date=October 1, 2019}}</ref> Over time, with White as president, the UFC developed into a highly successful business, and its gross revenue was $600 million in 2015.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.espn.com/mma/story/_/id/16970360/ufc-sold-unprecedented-4-billion-dana-white-confirms|title=UFC sold to WME-IMG in unprecedented deal|date=2016-07-11|website=ESPN.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-20}}</ref> In July 2016, Zuffa was sold to a consortium of investors led by [[William Morris Endeavor|WME-IMG]] for $4.025 billion. White owned 9% of the company at the time of the sale.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://usatoday30.usatoday.com/money/companies/management/2005-04-10-white-usat_x.htm|last=McCarthy |first=Michael |date=April 10, 2005|title=Battles yield winning 'Fighter'|work=[[USA Today]]|accessdate=March 25, 2007}}</ref> White announced he would continue in his role as president,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.businessinsider.com/mixed-martial-arts-league-ufc-sold-for-4-billion-to-wme-img-2016-7?r=UK&IR=T|last=O'Reilly |first=Lara |date= July 11, 2016 |title=The hugely popular mixed martial arts league UFC has been sold for $4 billion|work=[[Business Insider]]|accessdate=June 17, 2019}}</ref> and was given a stake in the new business.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.espn.com/mma/story/_/id/16970360/ufc-sold-unprecedented-4-billion-dana-white-confirms|title=UFC sold to WME-IMG in unprecedented deal|date=2016-07-11|website=ESPN.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-20}}</ref>\n\nIn May 2017, the UFC announced White would host ''[[Dana White's Tuesday Night Contender Series|Dana White's Contender Series]].'' Available exclusively through [[UFC Fight Pass]], the promotion\u2019s digital streaming service, and licensed separately from the UFC brand, the show allows up and coming fighters the chance to showcase their talents in hopes that one day they may compete in the UFC.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.foxsports.com/ufc/story/dana-white-receives-promoters-license-for-new-contender-series-separate-from-ufc-061417|last=Martin|first=Damon|date=June 14, 2017|title=Dana White receives promoter\u2019s license for new contender series separate from UFC|work=[[Fox Sports]]|accessdate=June 17, 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn March 18, 2019, White revealed that he had signed a new, seven-year contract to remain president of the UFC, as the UFC signed a deal with [[ESPN]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mmafighting.com/2019/3/18/18271731/dana-white-says-hes-extended-his-contract-with-the-ufc-for-seven-more-years|last=Raimondi |first=Marc |date=March 18, 2019|title=Dana White says he\u2019s extended his contract with the UFC for seven more years|work=[[MMA Fighting]]|accessdate=June 17, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.espn.com/mma/story/_/id/26301344/dana-white-agrees-new-7-year-deal-ufc|title=Dana White agrees to new 7-year deal with UFC|date=2019-03-19|website=ESPN.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-20}}</ref>\n\n===Loretta Hunt and GLAAD===\n\nIn 2009, White used expletives and derogatory language when referring to mixed martial arts reporter Loretta Hunt because he was upset with reporting and comments made by her.<ref name = YouTube_video>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Y0jFj4Cq1dc</ref> During his interview, White used expletives and an anti-gay slur when referring to sources for some of those reports.<ref name=YouTube_video/><ref>https://bleacherreport.com/articles/876197-dana-whites-hate-list-50-people-who-have-enraged-the-volatile-ufc-chief#slide40</ref><ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Y0jFj4Cq1dc</ref> GLAAD subsequently called for White and the UFC to apologize for his usage of that anti-gay slur. <ref>https://www.glaad.org/2009/04/01/dana-white-and-ufc-need-to-apologize</ref> While White later apologized and said that he \"regretted\" using the anti-gay slur, the Bleacher Report called his apology \"backhanded\".<ref>https://bleacherreport.com/articles/1164439-dana-white-the-five-dumbest-things-hes-said-in-recent-years#slide1</ref>\n\n===Boxing===\nWhite entered the boxing scene by co-promoting [[Floyd Mayweather Jr. vs. Conor McGregor]] due to McGregor being contracted to the UFC. In October 2017, White said at [[Freddie Roach (boxing)|Freddie Roach]]'s Wild Card West boxing club that he was \"getting into boxing, 100 percent.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.espn.com/mma/story/_/id/21341423/ufc-president-dana-white-interested-promoting-boxing-matches|last=Rafael|first=Dan|date=November 9, 2017|title=UFC president Dana White interested in promoting boxing matches|work=[[ESPN]]|accessdate=June 17, 2019}}</ref> White says that he wants to incorporate boxing into the company portfolio of the UFC.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sportsjoe.ie/mma/dana-white-planning-to-bring-boxing-to-the-ufc-141415|last=Murphy |first=Darragh|date=|title=Dana White planning to bring boxing to the UFC|work=Sports Joe|accessdate=June 17, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n* ''[[Ridiculousness (TV series)|Ridiculousness]]'', as himself, in episode: \"Dana White\" (2013)\n* ''[[The League]]'', as The Goon, in episode: \"Rafi and Dirty Randy\" (2013)\n* ''[[Silicon Valley (TV series)|Silicon Valley]]'', as Dana White, in episode \"Homicide\" (2015)\n* ''[[It's Always Sunny in Philadelphia]]'', as Dana White, in episode \"Wolf Cola: A Public Relations Nightmare\" (2017)\n\n==Personal life==\nWhite met his wife Anne ([[n\u00e9e]] Stella) when they were in the eighth grade and they married in 1996.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gq.com.au/men-of-the-year/event-coverage/everything-you-need-to-know-about-dana-white-before-his-gq-moty-appearance/image-gallery/8bffcf37a156c06986e40adb07fe6557|title=Everything You Need To Know About Dana White Before His GQ MOTY Appearance|last=Nash|first=Brad|date=November 9, 2018|website=GQ|language=en|access-date=October 1, 2019}}</ref> They have two sons, Dana III and Aidan, and one daughter, Savannah. White values his privacy, and keeps Anne out of the public spotlight.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://heavy.com/sports/2016/07/dana-white-net-worth-wife-anne-ufc-president-kids-mob-bio-about-family-salary-money/|title=Dana White, UFC President: 5 Fast Facts You Need to Know|last=Adams|first=Jonathan|date=2016-07-20|website=Heavy.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-20}}</ref> White bought a mansion in Pine Island Court, Las Vegas in 2006 from [[Frank Fertitta III]] for $1.95 million. White bought three other mansions in the same area from October 2016 to June 2017 for a combined total of around $6.2 million. Demolition permits were issued for the houses, presumably with the intent of creating a mega-mansion for White and his family.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.reviewjournal.com/business/housing/ufc-chief-dana-white-buys-3-homes-in-exclusive-las-vegas-area/|title=UFC chief Dana White buys 3 homes in exclusive Las Vegas area|date=June 6, 2017|website=Las Vegas Review-Journal|language=en-US|access-date=October 1, 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn 2011, White's mother, June, released the book ''Dana White, King of MMA: An Unauthorized Biography''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/12092479-dana-white-king-of-mma|last=White |first= June M. |date=|title=Dana White, King of Mma: Dana White an Unauthorized Biography|work=[[Goodreads]]|accessdate=June 17, 2019}}</ref> June claimed in the book that, since his success with the UFC, Dana had \"turned his back on his family and friends who were there for him when he needed help and support\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://fcfighter.com/dana-white%E2%80%99s-mom-calls-him-a-%E2%80%9Cp-%E2%80%9D-and-%E2%80%9Ctyrant%E2%80%9D-who-turned-his-back-on-his-family/|last=Molina |first=Joshua |date=July 19, 2011|title=Dana White\u2019s mom calls him a \"prick\" and \"tyrant,\" who turned his back on his family\n|work=Full Contact Fighter|accessdate=June 17, 2019}}</ref>\n\nWhite spoke at the [[2016 Republican National Convention]] in [[Cleveland, Ohio]], where he endorsed [[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]] nominee [[Donald Trump]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2016/jul/19/dana-white-speech-trump-republican-national-convention|title=UFC president Dana White stumps for Trump at Republican convention|work=[[The Guardian]]|date=July 19, 2016|accessdate=June 11, 2017}}</ref> White said that Trump helped the UFC at its beginnings, allowing the UFC to host its first event under Zuffa ownership ([[UFC 30]]) at the [[Trump Taj Mahal]] when others venues refused to host the UFC.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2018/aug/16/ufc-dana-white-donald-trump-relationship|title=Why the UFC is a perfect platform for Donald Trump\u2019s political ideology|last=Zidan|first=Karim|date=August 16, 2018|work=The Guardian|access-date=October 1, 2019|language=en-GB|issn=0261-3077}}</ref> White said, \"No arenas wanted us. This guy reached out, and he's always been a friend to me.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.washingtontimes.com/news/2018/aug/20/dana-white-on-loyalty-to-trump-that-guy-gave-us-ou/|title=UFC\u2019s Dana White on loyalty to Trump: \u2018That guy gave us our start when nobody would talk to us\u2019|last=|first=|date=|website=The Washington Times|language=en-US|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=October 1, 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn a season 15 episode of [[History (U.S. TV network)|History Channel's]] ''[[Pawn Stars]]'' (originally airing on February 5, 2018), White purchased over $60,000 worth of [[Katana]] swords including one of [[Rick Harrison]]'s 16th-century Japanese Katana.<ref>{{cite AV media|url=https://www.history.com/shows/pawn-stars/season-15/episode-17/dana-white-wants-ricks-1600s-japanese-katana||date= Feb 5, 2018|title=Dana White Wants Rick's 1600s Japanese Katana|medium=Reality |work=[[History Channel]]|accessdate=March 8, 2019}}</ref>\n\n=== Sex-tape lawsuit ===\nWhite was accused in a [[Celebrity sex tape|sex-tape scandal]], when a [[stripper]], allegedly taped a sexual encounter with White in [[Brazil]] around the year 2014 without his consent. The stripper also alleged White had been seeing her for months during his marriage.<ref name=\"suit\">{{cite web|url=https://canoe.com/sports/fighting/mma/stripper-filmed-sex-tape-with-dana-white-without-his-knowledge-suit-claims |date=April 5, 2020 |title=Stripper filmed sex tape with Dana White without his knowledge, suit claims |work=[[Canoe.com]] |access-date=April 5, 2020}}</ref>The stripper's live-in boyfriend then tried to [[Extortion|extort]] money from White, which resulted in a criminal case against her boyfriend.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cbssports.com/mma/news/ufc-president-dana-white-named-as-victim-in-200000-sex-tape-extortion-lawsuit/ |last=Campbell |first=Brian |date=April 4, 2020 |title=UFC president Dana White named as victim in $200,000 sex-tape extortion lawsuit |work=[[CBSSports.com]] |access-date=April 1, 2020}}</ref> In [[Nevada]], on April 3, 2020, a civil suit against White was filed, claiming he offered the boyfriend money to persuade him to plead guilty, in which White has denied.<ref name=\"suit\"/> According to the complaint, White paid $10,000 to the stripper to dance and have sex with him.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.reviewjournal.com/investigations/ufcs-dana-white-named-as-extortion-victim-in-sex-tape-case-1999477/ |last=German |first=Jeff |date=April 4, 2020 |title=UFC\u2019s Dana White named as extortion victim in sex-tape case |work=[[Las Vegas Review-Journal]] |access-date=April 5, 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Health issues===\nIn May 2012, White revealed that he had been diagnosed with [[M\u00e9ni\u00e8re's disease]], a neurological disorder.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://ca.sports.yahoo.com/news/mma--dana-white-diagnosed-with-meniere-s-disease-misses-first-live-ufc-card-in-11-years.html|last=Iole |first=Kevin |date=May 16, 2012|title=Dana White diagnosed with M\u00e9ni\u00e8re's disease, misses first live UFC card in more than 11 years|work=[[Yahoo Sports]]|accessdate=June 17, 2019}}</ref> He said, \"It's like [[vertigo]] but on steroids.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mmamania.com/2012/5/15/3023255/ufcs-dana-white-menieres-disease-ear-surgery-mma|title=UFCs Dana White reveals he has Meniere's disease|last=Jr|first=Adam Guillen|date=2012-05-15|website=MMAmania.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-20}}</ref> White claims that the disease was brought on because of a large fight he was involved in during his youth.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=C9e6cyv7lnw|last=Rogan |first=Joe|date=February 21, 2013|title=Joe Rogan Experience #327 - Dana White|work=[[YouTube]]|accessdate=June 17, 2019}}</ref>\n\nThe [[2012 in UFC#UFC on Fuel TV: Korean Zombie vs. Poirier|UFC on Fuel TV 3: Korean Zombie vs. Poirier]] event was to be the first he had missed in 11 years with White staying home, adhering to medical advice. White is undergoing [[Orthokine]] treatment for M\u00e9ni\u00e8re's disease, which he says has greatly reduced his symptoms.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mmamania.com/2013/4/18/4240318/dana-white-meniers-disease-a-rod-germany-stem-cell-treatment-cure-ufc-president|last=Guillen Jr.|first=Adam |date=April 18, 2013|title=Dana White Meniere's Disease: A-Rod, German stem cell treatment cure UFC President '100 percent'|work=[[SB Nation]]|accessdate=June 17, 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Charity===\nIn 2010, White donated $50,000 for a liver transplant to Tuptim Jadnooleum, the daughter of \u201cKru Nai\u201d Rattanachai, one of the instructors for Tiger Muay Thai and MMA in Phuket, Thailand.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://mmajunkie.usatoday.com/2018/01/ufc-dana-white-donation-saves-thai-girl-life |last=Marrocco |first=Steven |date=January 5, 2018 |title=Dana White opens up on $50,000 donation that helped save a young Thai girl's life |work=[[MMAjunkie.com]] |accessdate=October 12, 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn 2011, White donated $100,000 to his former high school to fund renovations to their athletic facilities.<ref name=\"knapp\"/>\n\n==Accomplishments==\n* Nevada Sportsman of the Year (2009)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090731110120/http://mmajunkie.com/news/15646/dana-white-honored-as-sportsman-of-the-year-while-250k-awarded-to-the-caring-place.mma|date=July 27, 2009|title=Dana White honored as \"Sportsman of the Year\" while $250K awarded to The Caring Place|work=[[MMAjunkie.com]]|accessdate=June 17, 2019}}</ref>\n* [[Wrestling Observer Newsletter Awards]]\n** [[Wrestling Observer Newsletter awards#Promoter of the Year|Promoter of the Year]] (2005\u201313; 2015\u201316)<ref>{{cite journal|last=Meltzer|first=Dave|authorlink=Dave Meltzer|date=March 6, 2017|title=March 6, 2017 Wrestling Observer Newsletter: 2016 Awards issue, talent departing TNA, more|journal=[[Wrestling Observer Newsletter]]|location=[[Campbell, California]]|issn=1083-9593|page=26}}</ref>\n* [[World MMA Awards]]\n** Leading Man of the Year (2008-19)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mmafighting.com/2019/7/3/20681393/world-mma-awards-2019-results|title=World MMA Awards 2019 Results|last=Tucker|first=Bryan|date=July 3, 2019|website=MMA Fighting|language=en|access-date=February 23, 2020}}</ref>\n* [[Armed Forces Foundation]]\n** Patriot Award<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mmamania.com/2009/03/19/ufcs-dana-white-accepts-patriot-award-for-humanitarian-efforts-to-raise-money-for-injured-soldiers|date=March 19, 2009|title=UFCs Dana White accepts Patriot Award for humanitarian efforts to raise money for injured soldiers|work=[[SB Nation]]|accessdate=June 17, 2019}}</ref>\n\n